The article discusses S. 3373, also known as the "Sergeant First Class Heath Robinson Honoring Our Promise to Address Comprehensive Toxics (PACT) Act of 2022." This act aims to amend various VA authorities related to healthcare and benefits for veterans who have been exposed to harmful environmental substances during their military service. It also addresses human resource matters and medical facility leases. The article expresses gratitude to Senators Tester and Moran, as well as Representatives Takano, Bost, and Ruiz, for their leadership in supporting this act.